reviews.headline: Great Fanning Effect
reviews.comments: I love the way this makes my eyelashes look. It really fans them out perfectly and I dont have any clumps at all. My only gripe is that is flakes on me all the time. I constantly have to wipe away little black specks from under my eye. It would be the perfect mascara if not for the flaking.

reviews.headline: Best mascara out there
reviews.comments: I love this mascara! I've tried so many different brands and formulas and so far it's the best; It separates, curls, and adds much needed volume.

reviews.headline: Very Impressed
reviews.comments: I received this as part of a free gift, and i may need to purchase in the future. only a couple of swipes needed in order to get the full effect. hasn't flaked yet and it hasnt made my lashes drop either.

reviews.headline: I would buy this again
reviews.comments: This is amazing mascara & does not irritate my allergies

reviews.headline: Clumps and flakes
reviews.comments: Had high hopes for this mascara. My mom loves it and I guess it doesnt do what it is doing to mine to hers. So I got it brand new. The brush is super fat and thick. Also once applying its instantly clumping amd thrm just flakes off through out the day. Then im having to pick black clumps out of my eyes. Wouldnt buy again.

reviews.headline: Perfect mascara
reviews.comments: Even though this does not claim to be water proof it stays on even with my weepy allergy eyes. And there is no flaking off and making raccoon eyes. Love it!

reviews.headline: Flaky
reviews.comments: Not for me at all - had high hopes. Weird brush and it was very flaky a few hours into the day.

reviews.headline: My favorite mascara ever
reviews.comments: This is the only mascara I will buy over and over again. It is soooo good. Makes my lashes so long and appear so thick. The curl will last all day and its still easy to take off with makeup remover. Absolutely worth the money!!! Always get compliments when I wear this mascara and I dont even have the longest lashes.

reviews.headline: Great clean mascara, weak as a mini
reviews.comments: I've  had problems over the last few months with mascaras by Maybelline and L'Oreal causing my eyes to tear and thus causing smeared mascara. This mascara is lengthening and no teary problems so far. It looses a star because the mini was either dried out, or so mini, that there's practically nothing it in which is frustrating. I'd rather pay $1-$2 more for something that I can really try out for several days.

reviews.headline: Dries out quickly
reviews.comments: This is an amazing mascara, unfortunately the product dries out after a handful of uses making it quite expensive. I started buying the mini because of this but I don't feel like I get as much use out of the product as I should. The first few applications are great, then after tha it starts to flake everywhere.

reviews.headline: My absolute fav !
reviews.comments: This mascara is a holy grail in my opinion ! It makes my short eyelashes look so long and full ! Definitely a must! I can't go a day without putting on this mascara and it also is very easy to clean off at the end of the day . Definitely highly recommended

reviews.headline: Not worth the hype
reviews.comments: Not sure what all the hype is about. It doesnt separate my lashes & just clumps them all together. Was really excited to try brvause I had heard such good things. Will nevrr buy again

reviews.headline: Buy the bigger one
reviews.comments: I LOVEEE ITTT SOOOO MUCHHHH

reviews.headline: The one for me
reviews.comments: This mascara makes my eyelashes look so full-I don't have to do much when I apply it. It comes off pretty decent when I wash my face and it doesn't dry out my lashes like other mascaras. So far this is my favorite from Benefit.

reviews.headline: I am a big fan
reviews.comments: I rarely do reviews on mascara because usually I am only a little impressed but this is my favorite I have ever used. You do have to do a few coats but it literally grabs every single lash and fans them out. No flaking for smudging. 20/10

reviews.headline: Disappointed
reviews.comments: This is the clumpiest mascara I've ever used in my life.  It takes me 10 minutes to do my eyes because I have to apply this so carefully and comb out every last.  It seems to come out in clumps rather than a cream.  I have been using different brushes to apply it; comb-like brushes, and that helps. The end result does leave me with elongated, curled lashes, but they're thin and kind of spidery.  I will use this because I paid a lot of money for it, but I get way better fluttery lashes from that old icon in the pink and green tube!

reviews.headline: Yay for no flakes!
reviews.comments: I don't write reviews often, but I needed to let people know how great this mascara is! After trying many different formulas, this one does not smear, flake, or dribble down when sweating. Today was 95 degrees and sunny in Georgia with 57% humidity (the ultimate test!) and this mascara STAYS PUT. I'm very impressed. 10/10

reviews.headline: Benefit Fan Fest
reviews.comments: It is ok - I was looking for the BadGals Bang and tried the Fan Fest but I like the BadGals Bamg much better!

reviews.headline: So disappointed
reviews.comments: Been looking for a good mascara. Tried this for the first time and immediately knew it wasnt the one‚Ä¶ as soon as the wand touched my lashes it dried up and flaked on me..crazy.

reviews.headline: Dries out quickly
reviews.comments: I loved this mascara a lot until it just dried out super fast. I did use it every single day for almost a month, it gave me amazing results with volume and fanning out lashes (my lashes already pretty long naturally).  After not using it for about two weeks, I decided to use it again and, to my surprise, it just simply dried out. Never had a mascara dried that fast, name brand or drug store ones.

faceoff_positive.comments: A Game-Changing Mascara gifted by Benefit cosmetics : Benefit's Fan Fest Fanning & Volumizing Mascara Review Rating: ‚òÖ‚òÖ‚òÖ‚òÖ‚òÖ I recently had the pleasure of trying out Benefit's new Fan Fest Fanning & Volumizing Mascara, and let me tell you, it's a game-changer! As an avid mascara enthusiast, I'm always on the lookout for products that deliver on their promises, and this mascara certainly exceeded my expectations. First and foremost, the formula is incredible. It's lightweight, yet incredibly buildable, allowing you to achieve both natural and dramatic looks with ease. The mascara glides onto the lashes smoothly, without clumping or smudging, giving you beautiful, defined lashes in just a few coats. What truly sets the Fan Fest Mascara apart is its unique brush design. The wand features a combination of short and long bristles that fan out your lashes while adding volume. This innovative design allows you to reach even the tiniest lashes in the corners of your eyes, ensuring a full and fluttery lash effect. I was amazed at how effortlessly the mascara coated each lash, creating a stunning fanned-out look that opened up my eyes. One of the standout features of this mascara is its long-lasting power. Once applied, it stays put throughout the day, resisting flaking and smudging. This is especially impressive considering how lightweight and comfortable it feels on the lashes. Whether I was at work, running errands, or attending social events, my lashes looked just as fresh and voluminous as when I first applied the mascara. Another aspect that impressed me was the mascara's ability to hold a curl. My lashes tend to straighten out quickly after using a lash curler, but with the Fan Fest Mascara, my curl remained intact all day long. This added an extra touch of elegance and made my eyes appear more awake and lifted. As for removal, the mascara is easily removed with a gentle eye makeup remover. I appreciated that it didn't require excessive rubbing or tugging
faceoff_positive.headline: Big fan üòç

faceoff_negative.comments: Don't get me wrong, this mascara does give length and volume and does hold a cure. HOWEVER, the price of the way it looks is so not worth your lashes health or the price. I notice that I can literally see the fibers of this mascara on my masked, it's like black dust, and it feels like fiber glass honestly. Sure it's cute and doesn't really come off, that's part of the problem. This formula is so dry that it dries out your lashed, its like when you use a clarifying shampoo on not greasy hair then don't use conditioner, my lashed were screaming. Not to mention trying to get all of this product off with water and makeup remover, even if you soak it, WILL make your lashes fall out. I used this a few times and it was visible that my lashed looked sparse after taking it off, not worth it.
